messages.title: TOWN CENTRE TRANSFORMATION CONTINUES
messages.content: Under the Conservatives new shops, restaurants and more jobs are coming to Woking. Commercial Way has been regenerated, a new indoor market opened and the Victoria Square development is progressing.

messages.title: DELIVERING EXCELLENT SERVICES
messages.content: Conservatives are continuing to deliver excellent services and value for money.

messages.title: FLOOD PREVENTION
messages.content: Conservative-led Woking Borough Council has earmarked funds to improve flood protection.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Ongoing regeneration of Woking under the Conservatives including the opening of Market Walk in autumn 2014 and plans for the new Victoria Square which will incorporate shops, restaurants, residential apartments, a medical centre and a hotel.
Opening of new businesses such as Bill’s, Carluccio’s and the Tante Marie Culinary Academy, and a new indoor market.
Progressing development of Victoria Square to include a new Marks & Spencer, bringing over 700 new jobs to Woking.
Investment in flood protection by the Conservative-led Woking Borough Council.

issues.economy: The new Victoria Square development will bring over 700 new jobs to Woking.
issues.governance: Continuing to deliver excellent services and value for money; earmarked funds for flood protection.

housing.content: The proposed new Victoria Square development has received planning approval and will include residential apartments.

images.caption: The popular new Market Walk opened in October 2014.
Artist's impression of the proposed Victoria Square development, incorporating the return of Marks & Spencer.
Commercial Way has been transformed under the Conservatives, pictured here outside the new Bill's restaurant.
